<dl style="margin-left: 2 em">
  <a name="dolmen"></a>
  <dt style="font-weight: bold">DOLMEN</dt>
  <dd>A type of single chamber Megalithic stone tomb originally (that is before excavation) buried within a mound. 
  <p>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d3925.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d3925.gif" alt="[example]" border="0" height="108" /></a>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d3573a.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d3573a.gif" alt="[example]" border="0" height="108" /></a>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d3573.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d3573.gif" alt="[example]" border="0" height="108" /></a>&nbsp;
  <br>
  <em>Flag of <a href="de-lg-01.html#ol">Oldendorf upon Luhe</a>, Germany (fotw); 
  Arms and Flag of <a href="pt-mcdss.html">Salselas</a>, Portugal (fotw) </em>
  </dd>
  
  <hr />
  <a name="doppelkreux"></a>
  <dt style="font-weight: bold">DOPPELKREUX</dt>
  <dd>See &lsquo;<a href="#doublearmedcross">double-armed cross 1)</a>&rsquo;. 
  <p>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d4062.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d4062.gif" alt="[example]" border="0" height="108" /></a>&nbsp;
  <br>
  <em>Flag of <a href="ch-sg072.html">Degersheim</a>, Switzerland (fotw)</em>
  </dd>
  
  <hr />
  <a name="dominicancross"></a>
  <dt style="font-weight: bold">DOMINICAN CROSS</dt>
  <dd>A cross fleury gyronny and symbol of the Dominican Order 
  � a cross of the Order of Santo Domingo or of St Dominic � see 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvcr.html#crossfleury">cross fleury</a>&rsquo; and 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvcr.html#crossgyronny">cross gyronny</a>&rsquo; with its following note (also 
  &lsquo;<a href="vxt-dvcq.html#crosscounterchanged">cross counterchanged</a>&rsquo;). 
  <p>
  <a href="../images/v/vxt-d1506.gif">
  <img src="../images/v/vxt-d1506.gif" alt="[example]" border="0" height="108" /></a>
